That Malice still is left behind
From her to this Recess I fled , And here my Life
me she's bent to wreak her Spite
me she's bent to wreak her Spite
She will not , will not stay behind

Fortune too may take her part , Exert her Strength , and show her Art ; With these the Vicious may combine , And favour their unjust Design ; But Virtue will the Shock sustain , And you'll unvanquished still remain : Your inward Joys will be secure , And you'll no Loss , nor Ill endure
my Love , And still my Choice
eternal Day , That dear , that welcome , blissful Shore Where I shall never suffer
! he cuts the yielding Air : Celestial Music sweetly plays , I hear
